@startuml Code_Review_States

' ============================================
' STATE DIAGRAM: Code Review Engagement Lifecycle
' Bug Bounty and Its Simulation Platform
' ============================================

title Code Review Engagement State Transitions

[*] --> Draft : Organization creates request

Draft --> Published : Publish request
Draft --> [*] : Cancel draft

Published --> Inviting : Send expert invitations
Inviting --> Assigned : Expert accepted
Inviting --> Cancelled : No responses (timeout)

Assigned --> In_Progress : Expert starts review
In_Progress --> Reviewing : Code analysis active
Reviewing --> Findings_Submitted : Issues documented
Findings_Submitted --> Report_Draft : Compile findings

Report_Draft --> Report_Submitted : Submit final report
Report_Submitted --> Under_Review : Org reviews report
Under_Review --> Clarification_Needed : Org requests clarification
Under_Review --> Approved : Org approves

Clarification_Needed --> Report_Submitted : Clarification provided
Approved --> Payment_Pending : Approve payment
Payment_Pending --> Paid : Payment processed
Paid --> Closed : Archive engagement

Cancelled --> [*]
Closed --> [*]

note right of Reviewing
  Review activities:
  - Static analysis
  - Security audit
  - Best practices check
  - Documentation review
end note

note right of Findings_Submitted
  Finding types:
  - Security vulnerabilities
  - Code quality issues
  - Performance problems
  - Best practice violations
end note

@enduml